CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 14, 1958, pg. A1 reads: "Before Robbers Came - The above picture was snapped about six weeks ago, while Kelly's Bar, last of the "Deep Wylie" taverns, was still doing business. Robbers visited the establishment on June 1, and two days later the mother-son partnership decided to fold up...Harris Photo.
TitMainTitle: Kelly's Bar with neon signs in window for Budweiser and Fort Pitt Beer on corner of Wylie Avenue and Fullerton Street, Hill District
